text:
FACILITATOR 2: At the beginning it was hard to align topics, because sometimes it felt fractured: you were talking about emotions and then we had to switch to nutrition. (Laughter)

FACILITATOR 4: I think it would have been better to plan together from the start, to co-design. When a program arrives "out of nowhere" by email, everything is already scheduled.

FACILITATOR 1: What I liked is that caregivers kept talking about the "Bloom time"  dedicating 15 minutes just to the child. It was simple and memorable.

FACILITATOR 3: I saw that when sessions included children through play, families engaged more. When it was lecture-heavy, babies got restless and people disengaged.
